Product description

I-ST STAGE R4 TEC WW - EN250A>10ᵒC.
(designed for diving in water temperatures above 10ᵒC)

> Lightweight, compact, multifunctional membrane-controlled first stage with wet chamber.

> The lack of an environmental diaphragm protects the R4 TEC WW from being 'overbalanced' (cutting off gas at greater depths).

> For supplying rebreathers, stage cylinders and classic configurations.

> Ideal for travelling

 

 

SPECIFICATIONS:
-balanced main valve
-wet chamber
-ports: 2x HP, 4x LP
-working pressure 300 bar
-material: chrome-coated maritime bronze
-weight 590 grams

 

WORKS WELL IN CONFIGURATIONS:
Stage cylinder - very good
Rebreather – perfect
Twinset - very good
Single – good
Sidemount - not recommended
